{
  "texts": [
    "Hybrid frameworks combine AI's learning capabilities with the reliability of deterministic test scripts.",
    "For instance, AI is used to monitor the effectiveness of test executions and update test scripts automatically when UI elements change.",
    "Other frameworks incorporate AI-based test oracles-mechanisms that determine whether a test passes or fails based on learned behavior or statistical profiles instead of hardcoded expectations.",
    "This expands testing coverage into non-deterministic or complex UI scenarios where traditional oracles may not suffice.",
    "A recurring theme in the literature is empirical validation."
  ]
}